Lafcadio is an object-relational mapping layer for Ruby and MySQL.

http://rubyforge.org/projects/lafcadio/

REQUIREMENTS:
* English Extensions ( http://englishext.rubyforge.org/ )
* Extensions ( http://extensions.rubyforge.org/ )
* QueueHash ( http://queuehash.rubyforge.org/ )
* log4r ( http://log4r.sourceforge.net/ )
* REXML ( http://www.germane-software.com/software/rexml/ ). If you're using Ruby 1.8 or later you already have REXML.
* Ruby DBI ( http://ruby-dbi.sourceforge.net/ )
* Ruby Month ( http://month.rubyforge.org/ )
* USCommerce ( http://uscommerce.rubyforge.org/ )

INSTALLATION:
As root, run "./install.rb", which will copy the Ruby files into the right
subdirectory. You can run "./install.rb --help" for information.